# Error Handling Patterns

## Decision Tree: Which Pattern to Use?

### For React Components

**Query errors (useQuery hooks):**

- Wrap component in `<ErrorBoundary>` - errors automatically caught
- Already have app-level boundary in `app/layout.tsx`
- Add feature-level boundaries for isolation

**Mutation errors (form submissions, button clicks):**

- Simple mutations → Use `useMutationWithErrorHandling` hook
- Complex error logic → Use try/catch with manual handling
- Need custom UI feedback → try/catch with state management

**Unexpected errors during render:**

- Already caught by app-level ErrorBoundary
- Add nested boundaries for feature isolation

### For Error Reporting

**Automatic (preferred):**

- ErrorBoundary catches query/render errors → auto-reports to Sentry
- `useMutationWithErrorHandling` catches mutation errors → auto-reports to Sentry

**Manual (when needed):**

- Caught errors you want to track → Use `captureException(error, context)`
- Add context breadcrumbs → Use `addBreadcrumb()`

## ErrorBoundary Usage

### Basic Usage

Wrap components that use queries or might throw errors:

```tsx
import { ErrorBoundary } from '@/components/error-boundary';

// ✅ Wrap component with queries
function ProfilePage() {
  return (
    <ErrorBoundary>
      <ProfileContent />
    </ErrorBoundary>
  );
}

function ProfileContent() {
  const user = useCurrentUser(); // If query throws, ErrorBoundary catches it

  if (!user) {
    return <div>Not found</div>;
  }

  return <div>{user.name}</div>;
}
```

### Custom Fallback UI

```tsx
import { ErrorBoundary } from '@/components/error-boundary';
import { CustomErrorUI } from './custom-error-ui';

// ✅ Custom fallback for specific feature
<ErrorBoundary fallback={CustomErrorUI}>
  <FeatureComponent />
</ErrorBoundary>;
```

### When to Add ErrorBoundary

- **App-level** - Already added in `app/layout.tsx` (catches all)
- **Feature-level** - Wrap complex features to isolate failures
- **Page-level** - Wrap individual pages that might fail independently

```tsx
// ✅ Feature isolation
<ErrorBoundary>
  <ComplexDataGrid />
</ErrorBoundary>

// ❌ Don't wrap everything individually
<ErrorBoundary>
  <SimpleButton />
</ErrorBoundary>
```

## Mutation Error Handling

### Using useMutationWithErrorHandling

Best for simple mutations with standard error handling:

```tsx
import { useMutationWithErrorHandling, getErrorMessage } from '@/lib/services/errors';
import { api } from '@/convex/_generated/api';

function CreateForm() {
  const { mutate, isLoading, error } = useMutationWithErrorHandling(api.items.create, {
    onSuccess: () => router.push('/items'),
  });

  const handleSubmit = async (data) => {
    await mutate(data); // Automatically reports errors to Sentry
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
      {error && <div className="error">{getErrorMessage(error)}</div>}
      <button disabled={isLoading}>Create</button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

### Using try/catch

For complex error handling or custom logic:

```tsx
import { getErrorMessage, isErrorCode, ErrorCode, captureException } from '@/lib/services/errors';

function CreateForm() {
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const create = useMutation(api.items.create);

  const handleSubmit = async (data) => {
    try {
      await create(data);
      router.push('/items');
    } catch (error) {
      // Check specific error codes
      if (isErrorCode(error, ErrorCode.DUPLICATE_SLUG)) {
        setError('title', { message: 'Already exists' });
        return;
      }

      // Manual Sentry reporting if needed
      captureException(error, {
        context: { operation: 'createItem', data },
        tags: { feature: 'items' },
      });

      setError(getErrorMessage(error));
    }
  };

  return <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>...</form>;
}
```

## Reading Error Information

### Get User-Friendly Message

```ts
import { getErrorMessage } from '@/lib/services/errors';

const message = getErrorMessage(error);
// Returns: User-friendly string for any error type
```

### Check Specific Error Code

```ts
import { isErrorCode, ErrorCode } from '@/lib/services/errors';

if (isErrorCode(error, ErrorCode.DUPLICATE_SLUG)) {
  // Handle duplicate specifically
}

if (isErrorCode(error, ErrorCode.AUTH_REQUIRED)) {
  redirect('/login');
}
```

### Get Error Code Directly

```ts
import { getErrorCode, ErrorCode } from '@/lib/services/errors';

const code = getErrorCode(error);
// Returns: ErrorCode enum value or UNKNOWN_ERROR
```

## Manual Error Reporting

### Report Caught Errors

```ts
import { captureException } from '@/lib/services/errors';

try {
  await riskyOperation();
} catch (error) {
  captureException(error, {
    context: {
      operation: 'riskyOperation',
      userId: user._id,
    },
    level: 'warning',
    tags: {
      feature: 'items',
    },
  });
}
```

### Add Breadcrumbs for Context

```ts
import { addBreadcrumb } from '@/lib/services/errors';

// Add breadcrumb before operation
addBreadcrumb({
  message: 'User clicked submit button',
  category: 'user-action',
  level: 'info',
});

// Errors after this point will include the breadcrumb
```

### Set User Context

```ts
import { setUserContext, clearUserContext } from '@/lib/services/errors';

// On login
setUserContext({
  id: user._id,
  email: user.email,
  username: user.name,
});

// On logout
clearUserContext();
```

## Available Error Codes

```ts
import { ErrorCode } from '@/lib/services/errors';

// Authentication & Authorization
ErrorCode.AUTH_REQUIRED; // Not authenticated
ErrorCode.FORBIDDEN; // No permission
ErrorCode.INVALID_CREDENTIALS;
ErrorCode.SESSION_EXPIRED;

// Validation
ErrorCode.DUPLICATE_SLUG; // Unique field conflict
ErrorCode.VALIDATION_FAILED; // Input validation failed
ErrorCode.INVALID_INPUT;
ErrorCode.MISSING_FIELD;

// Resource
ErrorCode.NOT_FOUND; // Resource doesn't exist

// System
ErrorCode.DATABASE_ERROR;
ErrorCode.NETWORK_ERROR;
ErrorCode.SERVER_ERROR;
ErrorCode.UNKNOWN_ERROR;
```

## Best Practices

### When to Use Each Pattern

**ErrorBoundary:**

- Query errors (always)
- React rendering errors
- Isolate complex features
- Display fallback UI automatically

**useMutationWithErrorHandling:**

- Simple mutations
- Want automatic Sentry reporting
- Standard error UI handling
- No complex error logic

**try/catch:**

- Need to check specific error codes
- Custom error handling logic
- Want to prevent error propagation
- Multiple different error paths

### Don't Report Expected Errors

```ts
// ✅ Expected case - don't report
const user = await getUser(userId);
if (!user) {
  return null; // Normal "not found" case
}

// ✅ Unexpected error - do report
try {
  await complexOperation();
} catch (error) {
  captureException(error); // Something went wrong
  throw error;
}
```

### Error Messages

- **Backend** - Throw structured errors with codes (see convex-errors.mdc)
- **Frontend** - Use `getErrorMessage()` for display
- **UI** - Show clear, actionable messages to users

## Quick Reference

```tsx
// Query errors - use ErrorBoundary
<ErrorBoundary>
  <ComponentWithQueries />
</ErrorBoundary>;

// Simple mutations - use hook
const { mutate, error } = useMutationWithErrorHandling(api.items.create, {
  onSuccess: () => {},
});

// Complex mutations - use try/catch
try {
  await mutation(data);
} catch (error) {
  if (isErrorCode(error, ErrorCode.DUPLICATE_SLUG)) {
    // Handle specific error
  }
  captureException(error);
}

// Get user-friendly message
const message = getErrorMessage(error);

// Add debugging context
addBreadcrumb({ message: 'User action', category: 'ui' });
```
